"{\"uid\": \"ign.com-articles-tom-cruise-will-reportedly-close-out-the-paris-olympics-with-a-stunt\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Tom Cruise will apparently be taking his stunts to the Olympic stage.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 69, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 10, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tom Cruise\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Cruise\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to reports in bothTMZandDeadlinetoday, the Top Gun and Mission: Impossible star is set to close out the ongoing Paris Olympics on August 11 with a stunt that will see him pass the flag to Los Angeles as 2028's host city.\", \"from\": 73, \"to\": 303, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 271, \"end\": 282, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999764399947, \"rank\": 1.640201745526988e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Per TMZ, the stunt involves Cruise \\\"rappelling down from the top of Stade de France ... landing on the stadium field and carrying the official Olympic flag.\\\"\", \"from\": 304, \"to\": 461, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 372, \"end\": 387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stade de France\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Expect a major Hollywood production,\\\" a source tells Deadline.\", \"from\": 463, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 479, \"end\": 488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999998277692306, \"rank\": 1.681784852250304e-07, \"text\": \"Hollywood\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cinema_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's been known for some time that the plan is for L.A. Mayor Karen Bass to accept the flag from Paris Mayor Anne Hidalgo in some sort of televised spectacle.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 685, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 578, \"end\": 582, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999890691582888, \"rank\": 1.0850182995522342e-05, \"text\": \"L.A.\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}, {\"begin\": 589, \"end\": 599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Karen Bass\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Karen_Bass\"}, {\"begin\": 624, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Mayor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/List_of_mayors_of_Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 636, \"end\": 648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Anne Hidalgo\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Anne_Hidalgo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"According to TMZ's report, that spectacle will also include a pre-recorded bit of Cruise skydiving down the Hollywood sign that was filmed back in March.\", \"from\": 687, \"to\": 840, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 700, \"end\": 703, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999999582157679, \"rank\": 4.1784205181643285e-08, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}, {\"begin\": 795, \"end\": 809, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some pararazzi photos circulated of Cruise on the Hollywood sign in March, although the connection between that and the Olympics wasn't made at the time.\", \"from\": 841, \"to\": 994, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 891, \"end\": 905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hollywood sign\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hollywood_Sign\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TMZ's report also adds that the stunt portion of Cruise's appearance is \\\"all very complicated,\\\" and Cruise may need a stunt double for the \\\"actual rappelling to kick this all off.\\\"\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1176, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 996, \"end\": 999, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 0.9999999582157679, \"rank\": 4.1784205181643285e-08, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reports are bolstered by the fact that Cruise has already had a presence at the Paris Olympics, being seen with other celebrities cheering on Simone Biles and Team USA in the gymnastic events on day 2.\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1383, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's also not the first time Cruise has been involved in an Olympic ceremony;in 2004, he was one of the celebrity torch-bearers in Los Angeles.\", \"from\": 1384, \"to\": 1527, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1526, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.9999999764399947, \"rank\": 1.640201745526988e-08, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Alex Stedman is a Senior News Editor with IGN, overseeing entertainment reporting.\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1529, \"end\": 1533, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"score\": 0.9983084669099641, \"rank\": 0.0016795024292072388, \"text\": \"Alex\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Alex_Rousseau\"}, {\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IGN\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"IGN\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IGN\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/IGN\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When she's not writing or editing, you can find her reading fantasy novels or playing Dungeons & Dragons.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1717, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not yet available for streaming.\", \"from\": 1719, \"to\": 1751, \"entities\": []}]}"